./dissolve-workspace/runs/solo/codex/codex.stderr.log:969:+    <p class="verdict">With the loaded label removed, the original question becomes a bundle of sharper questions about recurring harmful drinking, impaired control, sustaining mechanisms, intervention results, remaining agency, and response policy. The remaining bare question, "but does it belong to the special category?", is empty once those observations are fixed.</p>
./dissolve-workspace/runs/solo/codex/codex.stderr.log:970:+    <p>For the surviving decision question, settle by consequences. A useful stance treats the pattern as harmful and partly self-propelling while preserving practical accountability: reduce triggers, offer effective help, keep boundaries, require repair where repair helps, and use blame only where blame improves prediction, prevention, or restitution. "What is deserved in the hidden essence sense?" adds no testable handle; "what response helps?" does the work.</p>
./dissolve-workspace/runs/solo/codex/codex.stderr.log:975:-      <li>Value work remains: choose rules for blame, repair, coercion, coverage, and accommodation.</li>
./dissolve-workspace/runs/solo/codex/codex.stderr.log:980:+      <li>Policy still contains tradeoffs among compassion, safety, autonomy, trust, cost, and repair; those are decisions to make openly.</li>
./dissolve-workspace/runs/solo/codex/codex.stderr.log:1040:+    <p>Two internal handles collide. One handle says: drinking is an action performed by a person; actions invite responsibility, incentives, trust, blame, apology, and repair. The other says: repeated drinking can keep happening after sincere vows, losses, shame, withdrawal, craving, and visible harm; that looks less like ordinary preference and more like a process that has partly escaped simple command. The word <em>disease</em> is asked to settle that collision by category membership. The territory contains patterns, mechanisms, choices, harms, and interventions. The map-confusion is asking one word to distribute all the moral and practical consequences.</p>
